04/07/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- According to results of a survey released Thursday (3 July), Macedonians consider political parties to be the most corrupt groups in the state. 
Transparency International's Global Corruption Barometer survey found that 28.2 per cent believe parties are the most corrupt, compared to 17.9 per cent who chose customs officials and 9.4 per cent who chose the courts.
In other news, the country's largest labour union, the Macedonian Trade Unions' Federation (SSM), is threatening to organise a series of protests against poor living standards. 
SSM is demanding a meeting with a government representative by mid-month.
Also Thursday, a delegation of Macedonia's main opposition party, VMRO-DPMNE, met with EU security chief Javier Solana in Brussels. 
They discussed recent developments in the country, including expected layoffs at the power company. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 04/07/03; MIA, A1 TV - 03/07/03)
